John Drosdick

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search






This biography of a living person needs additional citations for verification. Please help by adding reliable sources. Contentious material about living persons that is unsourced or poorly sourced must be removed immediately, especially if potentially libelous or harmful. (February 2016) (Learn how and when to remove this template message)


John G. Drosdick is an American businessman.
Since May 2000, he has been President, Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of the Board of Directors of Sunoco Inc. (a Philadelphia-based company concentrating on refining and retailing petroleum and petrochemical products).[1] As of 2006, he was the fifteenth-highest-paid chief executive officer in the United States.[2]
He is also chairman of the Board of Trustees of Villanova University[1] and serves on the boards of directors of H. J. Heinz Company and U.S. Steel.[3]
Drosdick received a Bachelor of Science degree in chemical engineering from Villanova and a Master of Science degree in chemical engineering from the University of Massachusetts Amherst.[4]
