Subsidiaries









Business Information
															The group's principal activities are petroleum refiner, marketer and chemicals manufacturer with interests in logistics and cokemaking. The group operates in five segments: refining and supply segment manufactures and markets petroleum products. The retail marketing segment sells gasoline and middle distillates. The chemical segment manufactures, distributes and markets commodity and intermediate petrochemicals. The logistics segment operates refined product, crude oil pipelines and terminals. The coke segment consists of blast-furnace coke manufacturing at sunoco's Indiana harbor facility in east Chicago, in and jewell facility in vansant, va, and produces metallurgical coal from mines in Virginia. The group operates in the United States, northeast, midwest, south central regions, Virginia and Indiana. On 13-Jan-2004 the group completed the purchase of eagle point refinery and related assets from el paso corporation.   
															






                       
