About:
	    John Drosdick


	    An Entity of Type : person,
	    from Named Graph : http://dbpedia.org,
	    within Data Space : dbpedia.org






John G. Drosdick is an American businessman. Since May 2000, he has been President, Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of the Board of Directors of Sunoco Inc. (a Philadelphia-based company concentrating on refining and retailing petroleum and petrochemical products). As of 2006, he was the fifteenth-highest-paid chief executive officer in the United States. He is also chairman of the Board of Trustees of Villanova University and serves on the boards of directors of H. J. Heinz Company and U.S. Steel.





Property
Value

dbo:abstract

John G. Drosdick is an American businessman. Since May 2000, he has been President, Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of the Board of Directors of Sunoco Inc. (a Philadelphia-based company concentrating on refining and retailing petroleum and petrochemical products). As of 2006, he was the fifteenth-highest-paid chief executive officer in the United States. He is also chairman of the Board of Trustees of Villanova University and serves on the boards of directors of H. J. Heinz Company and U.S. Steel. Drosdick received a Bachelor of Science degree in chemical engineering from Villanova and a Master of Science degree in chemical engineering from the University of Massachusetts Amherst. (en)
