Executive Profile
John G. Drosdick  Director, Triumph Group, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships73$95,000
Background

		Mr. John G. Drosdick, also known as Jack, served as President of Sunoco Inc. from December 1996 to August 8, 2008 and Chief Executive Officer from May 2000 to August 8, 2008. Mr. Drosdick served as the Chief Operating Officer of Sunoco Inc. (Formerly Sun Company Inc.) from December 1996 to May 2000. Mr. Drosdick served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Tosco Corp. He served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Ultramar Inc. from 1992 to 1996. ... He served as the President and Chief Operating Officer of Ultramar Corporation from 1990 to 1996. He also worked with Hercules Incorporated. He began his career with Exxon Corporation in 1968 and held a wide variety of management positions for 15 years. He served as the Non-Executive Chairman of Sunoco Inc., subsidiary of Sunoco Logistics Partners LP from May 2000 to December 31, 2008. He served as the Chairman of the Board of Trustees at Villanova University since 2001. He served as Chairman at Sunoco Partners LLC, the General Partner of Sunoco Logistics Partners LP, from October 2001 to October 2008. He has been Independent Director at United States Steel Corporation since February 25, 2003. He has been a Director at Triumph Group, Inc. since November 9, 2012. He served as an Independent Director of Hawk Acquisition Intermediate Corporation II (formerly H. J. Heinz Co.), from December 1, 2005 to June 2013. He serves as a Director of Ultramar Corporation. Mr. Drosdick served as a Director of Sunoco Inc. from December 1996 to December 2008. He served as a Director of H. J. Heinz Company until June 7, 2013. He served as a Director of Lincoln National Corporation from 2000 to May 12, 2005. He served as a Director of GE Betz, Inc. (Formerly BetzDearborn Inc.) since December 1997. He serves on the Board of Trustees of the Philadelphia Museum of Art and Kimmel Center for the Performing Arts. Mr. Drosdick graduated from Villanova University with a B.Sc. Degree in Chemical Engineering and received a M.Sc. in Chemical Engineering from the University of Massachusetts.Read Full Background




